    "content": "## 🏗️ HTML5: The Skeleton of the Web\n\nHTML (HyperText Markup Language) provides the **structure** of a webpage. HTML5 is the current standard and focuses heavily on **semantic meaning** — using elements that describe WHAT content is, not just HOW it looks.\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Document Structure\n\nEvery valid HTML5 document starts with this boilerplate:\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"A description of this page\">\n  <title>My Page Title</title>\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">\n</head>\n<body>\n  <!-- Content goes here -->\n  <script src=\"app.js\" defer></script>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n- `<!DOCTYPE html>`: Tells the browser it's HTML5.\n- `<head>`: Metadata, styles, and script links.\n- `<body>`: Everything visible on the page.\n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Semantic HTML5 Tags\n\nSemantic tags tell the browser (and web crawlers) what role content plays:\n\n| Tag | Purpose |\n|-----|---------|\n| `<header>` | Top of page or section (logo, nav) |\n| `<nav>` | Navigation links |\n| `<main>` | The primary content of the page (unique, only one per page) |\n| `<section>` | A thematic grouping of content |\n| `<article>` | A self-contained piece of content (blog post, news item) |\n| `<aside>` | Sidebar, related links |\n| `<footer>` | Bottom of page or section |\n| `<figure>` + `<figcaption>` | An image/diagram with a caption |\n\n**Why semantics matter:**\n- **SEO**: Search engines rank semantically correct pages higher.\n- **Accessibility**: Screen readers navigate by semantic tags.\n- **Maintainability**: Code is easier for humans to understand.\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Headings: The Hierarchy\n\nHeadings (`<h1>` - `<h6>`) create a document outline:\n- **Rule**: Only ONE `<h1>` per page (the main topic).\n- Use headings in order (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`) — don't skip levels.\n\n```html\n<h1>MERN Fullstack Bootcamp</h1>\n  <h2>Phase 1: Web Foundations</h2>\n    <h3>Lesson 6: HTML5 Mastery</h3>\n```\n\nScreen readers and SEO tools read this hierarchy.\n\n---\n\n## 4️⃣ Links and Images\n\n```html\n<!-- Link: opens in same tab -->\n<a href=\"/about\">About Us</a>\n\n<!-- Link: opens in NEW tab -->\n<a href=\"https://google.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Google</a>\n\n<!-- Image: alt text is MANDATORY for accessibility -->\n<img src=\"profile.jpg\" alt=\"Mwero Abdalla profile photo\" width=\"300\">\n```\n\n`rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"` prevents security vulnerabilities when opening links in a new tab.\n\n---\n\n## 5️⃣ Lists\n\n```html\n<!-- Unordered (bullet points) -->\n<ul>\n  <li>HTML</li>\n  <li>CSS</li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- Ordered (numbered) -->\n<ol>\n  <li>First, write HTML</li>\n  <li>Then, style with CSS</li>\n</ol>\n\n<!-- Definition list -->\n<dl>\n  <dt>API</dt>\n  <dd>Application Programming Interface</dd>\n</dl>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6️⃣ Forms and User Input\n\nForms are essential for collecting user data:\n\n```html\n<form method=\"POST\" action=\"/submit\">\n  <label for=\"email\">Email:</label>\n  <input type=\"email\" id=\"email\" name=\"email\" required placeholder=\"you@example.com\">\n\n  <label for=\"password\">Password:</label>\n  <input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" name=\"password\" minlength=\"8\" required>\n\n  <label for=\"country\">Country:</label>\n  <select id=\"country\" name=\"country\">\n    <option value=\"ke\">Kenya</option>\n    <option value=\"ug\">Uganda</option>\n  </select>\n\n  <label for=\"bio\">Bio:</label>\n  <textarea id=\"bio\" name=\"bio\" rows=\"4\"></textarea>\n\n  <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n</form>\n```\n\n**Input types:** `text`, `email`, `password`, `number`, `date`, `checkbox`, `radio`, `file`, `range`, `color`.\n\n**Validation attributes:** `required`, `minlength`, `maxlength`, `pattern`, `min`, `max`.\n\n---\n\n## 7️⃣ Media\n\n```html\n<video src=\"intro.mp4\" controls autoplay muted loop>\n  Your browser doesn't support video.\n</video>\n\n<audio src=\"podcast.mp3\" controls>\n  Your browser doesn't support audio.\n</audio>\n\n<!-- Embed external content -->\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" \n  src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/abc123\"\n  title=\"YouTube video player\"\n  allowfullscreen>\n</iframe>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8️⃣ Tables\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Name</th>\n      <th>Score</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Mwero</td>\n      <td>95%</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9️⃣ Data Attributes\n\nCustom HTML attributes for storing extra data:\n\n```html\n<button data-user-id=\"123\" data-action=\"delete\">Delete User</button>\n```\n\n```javascript\nconst btn = document.querySelector('button')\nconsole.log(btn.dataset.userId)   // \"123\"\nconsole.log(btn.dataset.action)   // \"delete\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## �� Key Rules\n\n| Rule | Why It Matters |\n|------|---------------|\n| Only one `<h1>` per page | SEO and accessibility |\n| Always include `alt` on images | Accessibility and SEO |\n| Use semantic tags | Readability, SEO, accessibility |\n| Match every `<label>` to an `<input>` via `for`/`id` | Accessibility (clicking label focuses input) |\n| Use `rel=\"noopener\"` on external links | Security |",
